  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\nwhen i calling a contract function that contains calling another contract, it will always throw this error\r\nError: VM Exception while processing transaction: revert\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nhere are the core functions of the two contracts,i deployed them and write the test script:\r\ncontract A is  like: \r\n```\r\ncontract A {\r\n    mapping(address => address) public map;\r\n    uint public  i = 1;\r\n    address public i = 0x912312312...;\r\n    \r\n    function test() public view returns(bool) {\r\n        return true;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\ncontract B is  likeï¼š \r\n```\r\nimport \"./A.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract B {\r\n      A a = A(0x.......);\r\n      \r\n     function calltest() public view returns (bool) {\r\n            return a.test();\r\n      } //call this function will fail\r\n   \r\n     function getI () public view returns(uint) {\r\n        return a.i();\r\n    }   // call this function will success\r\n\r\n     function getMap (address addr) public view returns(address) {\r\n        return a.map(addr);\r\n    }   // call this function will fail\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nall function should run correctly\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nwhen B calls a public variable of A, it always succeed; but call a public function or call a mapping or an array, it will fail. I've tried many versions of truffle.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\nMacOS 10.13.6 Beta\r\nTruffle v4.0.6 (core: 4.0.6) ~ Truffle v4.1.11\r\nSolidity v0.4.19 (solc-js) ~ Solidity v0.4.24\r\nnpm v6.2.0\r\nnode v10.5.0\r\n\r\n",
